Seriki Adinoyi in Jos As farming season sets in, the Senator Representing Plateau South in the National Assembly, Professor Ladi Dadu’ut, has distributed empowerment items worth millions of Naira to over 600 of her constituents. Speaking at the distribution ceremony in Shendam yesterday, Senator Dadu’ut said the gesture was her own way of showing appreciation to her constituents for finding her worthy to represent them in the Senate. Items distributed by the senator includeed power tillers and water pump for dry season farming. Other items distributed were motorcycles, tricycles, sewing machines, grinding machines, knapsack among others. She said that she has empowered over 8,000 of her constituents since she was elected senator about a year ago. She said: “As you are aware during my manifesto, I pledged to focus on the priority areas of agriculture, education, women and youths empowerment, health, and human capital development. In line with my commitment to deliver on the dividends of democracy to the good people of my constituency, I have committed myself to fulfilling this promise. Calling on her constituents and the people of the state to support the Simon Lalong’s administration, Dadu’ut stressed that she has enjoyed tremendous support from the governor. Daduut also appreciated President Muhammadu Buhari led federal government for its economic policies that have been yielding desired results. The First Lady of Plateau State, Mrs. Regina Lalong, lauded the great achievements of the Ssnator in just one year in office. Represented by Rebecca Sambo, commissioner of women affairs in the state, the first lady pledged to support the senator in order for her to continue to provide dividends of democracy to the people of the senatorial district.